{"symbol": "METAP2", "uniprot": "P50579", "protein_name": "Methionine aminopeptidase 2", "length": 478, "function": "Cotranslationally removes the N-terminal methionine from nascent proteins. The N-terminal methionine is often cleaved when the second residue in the primary sequence is small and uncharged (Met-Ala-, Cys, Gly, Pro, Ser, Thr, or Val). The catalytic activity of human METAP2 toward Met-Val peptides is consistently two orders of magnitude higher than that of METAP1, suggesting that it is responsible for processing proteins containing N-terminal Met-Val and Met-Thr sequences in vivo", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000111142", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.3911, "protein_drug": 0.571, "rna_drug": 0.86}, "flags": {"surface": false, "enzyme": true, "mod_aso": true, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "ASO", "winning_axis": "RNA", "quadrant": "Both viable", "best_route": "small molecule", "sm_score": "0.721", "sirna_score": "0.742", "aso_score": "0.763"}, "modality": "ASO", "structure": "data/structures/METAP2.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.695, "volume": 826.8, "residues": [14, 219, 220, 222, 230, 231, 251, 262, 327, 328, 329, 331, 338, 339, 343, 364, 366, 382, 383, 384, 414, 443, 444, 445, 447, 457, 459]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.028, "volume": 433.8, "residues": [133, 135, 136, 137, 138, 139, 285, 288, 289, 469, 471, 474]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.017, "volume": 328.6, "residues": [112, 113, 114, 116, 178, 181, 182, 185]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/P50579"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "AlphaFold", "url": "https://alphafold.ebi.ac.uk/entry/P50579"}, {"key": "opentargets", "label": "Open Targets", "url": "https://platform.opentargets.org/target/ENSG00000111142"}, {"key": "genecards", "label": "GeneCards", "url": "https://www.genecards.org/cgi-bin/carddisp.pl?gene=METAP2"}, {"key": "ensembl", "label": "Ensembl", "url": "https://www.ensembl.org/Homo_sapie